The United Democratic Alliance (UDA) party has
invited all three presidential aspirants for interviews ahead of the August
polls. The contestants namely; Deputy President
William Ruto, Tracy Wanjiru and Orina Jephanei, were called to appear before
the party officials for vetting on Saturday at the Husler Center in Nairobi. UDA Secretary General Veronica Maina, in a
statement on Thursday, acknowledged the applications of the trio for the
party’s ticket through nominations in the forthcoming delegates conference. "We are in receipt of your application
to be nominated as a Presidential Candidate under United Democratic Alliance
political party,” Ms. Maina wrote. “We write to invite you for verification of
documents and interview to determine your eligibility as a Presidential
Candidate. This will be held on Saturday, March 12. 2022 at 8:30 am, the venue
being Hustler Plaza.” The SG directed the candidates to produce
original national IDs, proof of payment of nomination fees, original and copies
of academic certificates. Other requirements during the interview are
an updated resume and a soft copy of a coloured passport. For Orina Jephanei who had requested a waiver
of nomination fees, Ms. Maina advised the presidential hopeful to present his
petition at 10am on the same platform. UDA’s nomination fees for the presidency was
Ksh.1 million.  The party is set to hold its NDC on March 15,
2022 at the Kasarani indoor arena in Nairobi.